body: If hate speech isn't protected under free speech then there is no free speech, and the phrase means nothing. This site isn't dead, it's just new/young. There's a difference. And most people don't go on Twitter and Reddit. It's just that they stopped posting there and went elsewhere, or they went silent rather than face the backlash. I've lost a few rep points in the past hour alone for speaking out against the brigaders coming in to discredit us from Voat posting racist bullshit. They're making a concerted effort to destroy what the builders are building because their own site is so boring. You can only post "Yeah, I agree" so many times before it's boring as hell. And that's what Reddit is going to become. When everyone who disagrees has gone silent, and all you have left are a bunch of sheeple agreeing with one another, even the Agreers are going to fall away. There'll be nothing to left to discuss, no more give and take, just people like you saying, Oooooh, I'm so woke. Yeah, me too. What then? What's left for you to say?
